    "It is possible that some new gene-disease associations may only be discovered once we can confidently call more complex variants present in understudied genes that are previously not associated with any MDs [59,60].",
    "Nonetheless, we are still limited in our ability to identify and interpret complex structural variants and variants in non-protein coding regions [61][62][63].",
    "Furthermore, the resulting phenotype could be driven by various factors, such as genetic and epigenetic modifiers [51,[64][65][66][67].",
